    "avalancheActivity" : {
      "highlights" : "HIGH avalanche danger outside of ski runs",
      "comment" : "Intensive precipitation and storm-strength winds will lead to high avalanche danger above 2000m. Avalanches can easily be triggered by one single winter sports enthusiast in all aspecdts and then grow to to large size. Danger zones occur on steep slopes near to and distant from ridgelines, behind drops in the landscape and in wind-loaded gullies and bowls. Frequency and spread of avalanche prone locations increase with ascending altitude. Also naturally triggered avalanches can be expected. The danger is especially acute in alpine terrain where winter sports are practiced. Whumpf noises and fractures which appear when treading upon the snowpack, as well as freshly released avalanches are alarm signals. Activities in outlying terrain demand restraint. The inexperienced should not leave secured ski runs."
    },
